472
00:44:09,199 --> 00:44:13,478
Y'all got 10 clicks
to go to that river. Move out.

473
00:44:14,079 --> 00:44:19,916
- One, two, hup!
- Step it up! Look alive out there.

474
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:23,514
The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always someplace to go.

475
00:44:23,599 --> 00:44:25,510
Fire in the hole!

476
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:30,789
Gump, check out that hole.

477
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:33,677
And there was always something to do.

478
00:44:33,760 --> 00:44:36,637
Mount 'em up!
Spread out! Cover his back!

479
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:47,309
One day it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.

480
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:50,472
We've been through every
kind of rain there is.

481
00:44:50,559 --> 00:44:57,032
Little bitty stinging rain
and big old fat rain,

482
00:44:57,119 --> 00:45:01,398
rain that flew in sideways,
and sometimes rain even seemed

483
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:04,835
to come straight up from underneath.

484
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:08,195
Shoot, it even rained at night.

485
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:11,077
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

486
00:45:11,159 --> 00:45:14,755
I'm going to lean up against you.
You lean up against me.

487
00:45:14,840 --> 00:45:18,913
This way we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

488
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:21,434
You know why
we're a good partnership, Forrest?

489
00:45:21,519 --> 00:45:26,469
'Cause we be watching out for one
another, like brothers and stuff.

490
00:45:28,239 --> 00:45:31,789
Hey, Forrest,
something I been thinking about.

491
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:34,713
I got a very important question
to ask you.

492
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:40,074
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

493
00:45:41,679 --> 00:45:44,672
- OK.
- Man, I tell you what.

494
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:46,954
I got it all figured out, too.

495
00:45:47,039 --> 00:45:49,838
So many pounds of shrimp
will pay off the boat.

496
00:45:49,920 --> 00:45:53,070
So many pounds for gas.
We'll live right on the boat.

497
00:45:53,159 --> 00:45:55,389
We ain't got to pay no rent.

498
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:59,188
We can just work it together, split
everything right down the middle.

499
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:04,273
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50. Hey,
Forrest, all the shrimp you can eat.

500
00:46:05,840 --> 00:46:08,228
That's a fine idea.

501
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:10,958
Bubba did have a fine idea.

502
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:17,556
I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

503
00:46:17,639 --> 00:46:21,188
I sent her letters.
Not every day, but almost.

504
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:25,795
I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

505
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:28,838
and told her
how I thought about her always.

506
00:46:30,199 --> 00:46:33,987
And how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

507
00:46:34,079 --> 00:46:36,833
just as soon as she had the time.

508
00:46:36,920 --> 00:46:39,672
I'd always let her know
that I was OK.

509
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:46,791
Then I'd sign each letter
"Love, Forrest Gump."

510
00:47:00,280 --> 00:47:03,635
This one day,
we was out walking like always,

511
00:47:03,719 --> 00:47:09,396
and then, just like that,
somebody turned off the rain,

512
00:47:09,480 --> 00:47:11,914
and the sun come out.

513
00:47:13,679 --> 00:47:17,036
Ambush! Take cover!

514
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:30,510
- Get that pig up here, God damn it!
- Forrest, are you OK?

515
00:47:33,119 --> 00:47:35,349
Strong Arm, Strong Arm!

516
00:47:37,400 --> 00:47:42,076
- We've got a man down.
- Strong Arm, this is Leg Lima 6!

517
00:47:42,159 --> 00:47:46,835
Roger, Strong Arm! We have incoming
from the treeline at Point Blue...

518
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:50,356
...plus two! A.K. S and rockets!
We're getting it hard!

519
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:54,592
- Misfire! Misfire!
- God damn it!

520
00:47:56,199 --> 00:47:59,987
Get that pig unfucked
and put it in the treeline!

521
00:48:01,679 --> 00:48:04,068
They got us down, hard and hurt.

522
00:48:04,159 --> 00:48:07,630
We're going to move back
to the blue line.

523
00:48:08,559 --> 00:48:10,436
Pull back! Pull back!

524
00:48:10,639 --> 00:48:14,315
- Forrest! Run, Forrest!
- Pull back!

525
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:18,711
- Run! Run, man! Run!
- Pull back, Gump!

526
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:23,193
Run, God damn it! Run!

527
00:48:48,159 --> 00:48:52,072
I ran and ran
just like Jenny told me to.

528
00:48:55,119 --> 00:49:00,672
I ran so far so fast that soon I was
all by myself, which was a bad thing.

529
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:08,751
Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure he was OK.

530
00:49:17,440 --> 00:49:19,829
Where the hell are you?

531
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:27,472
And on my way back to find Bubba,
there was a boy laying on the ground.

532
00:49:27,559 --> 00:49:31,438
Tex. OK.

533
00:49:31,960 --> 00:49:35,668
I couldn't let him lay there
all alone, scared the way he was,

534
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:39,115
so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

535
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:56,552
Every time I went back
looking for Bubba,

536
00:49:56,639 --> 00:50:00,791
somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest, help me!"

537
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:09,150
OK. Here. Here.

538
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:14,233
No sweat, man.
Lay back. You'll be OK.

539
00:50:16,360 --> 00:50:20,751
I started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.

540
00:50:20,840 --> 00:50:26,472
I know my position is danger close!
We got Charlie all over this area.

541
00:50:26,559 --> 00:50:29,358
I got to have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

542
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:31,670
Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

543
00:50:31,760 --> 00:50:36,072
I know he's dead! My whole
goddamn platoon is wiped out!

544
00:50:36,159 --> 00:50:40,869
God damn it! What are you doing?
You leave me here!

545
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:44,349
Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

546
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:47,954
God, I said leave me here,
God damn it!

547
00:50:48,039 --> 00:50:50,429
Leg Lima six, this is strong-arm.

548
00:50:50,519 --> 00:50:53,431
Be advised your fast
movers are inbound. Over.

549
00:50:53,599 --> 00:50:56,557
Then it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.

550
00:50:56,639 --> 00:50:59,199
Something bit me!

551
00:51:06,119 --> 00:51:07,951
Goddamn son of a bitch!

552
00:51:09,199 --> 00:51:14,990
I can't leave the platoon.
I told you to leave me there, Gump.

553
00:51:15,079 --> 00:51:19,197
Forget about me. Get yourself out!
Did you hear what I said?

554
00:51:19,280 --> 00:51:23,592
Gump, damn it, put me down.
Get your ass out of here.

555
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:29,197
I didn't ask you to pull me out
of there, God damn you!

556
00:51:29,280 --> 00:51:32,476
- Where do you think you're going?
- To get Bubba.

557
00:51:32,559 --> 00:51:34,516
I got an air strike
inbound right now.

558
00:51:34,599 --> 00:51:38,956
They're going to nape the whole area.
Stay here! That's an order.

559
00:51:39,039 --> 00:51:41,429
I gotta find Bubba!

560
00:52:06,639 --> 00:52:09,393
I'm OK, Forrest. I'm OK.

561
00:52:17,480 --> 00:52:21,233
- Bubba, no.
- I'll be all right.

562
00:52:29,320 --> 00:52:32,072
Come on. Come on. Come on.

563
00:52:36,639 --> 00:52:38,391
I'm OK, Forrest.

564
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:43,077
I'm OK. I'm fine.

565
00:53:18,199 --> 00:53:21,112
Top smoke. Get it up there.

566
00:53:21,320 --> 00:53:25,393
If I'd have known this was going
to be the last time me and Bubba

567
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:28,755
was gonna talk, I'd of thought
of something better to say.

568
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:32,719
- Hey, Bubba.
- Hey, Forrest.

569
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:40,795
- Forrest, why did this happen?
- You got shot.

570
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:46,072
Then Bubba said something
I won't ever forget.

571
00:53:46,159 --> 00:53:48,798
I want to go home.

572
00:53:49,639 --> 00:53:52,996
Bubba was my best good friend.

573
00:53:53,079 --> 00:53:57,596
And even I know that ain't something
you can find just around the corner.

574
00:53:57,679 --> 00:54:00,797
Bubba was going to be
a shrimping boat captain,

575
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:05,112
but instead, he died right
there by that river in Vietnam.

576
00:54:09,079 --> 00:54:11,036
That's all I have to say about that.

577
00:54:14,280 --> 00:54:16,952
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

578
00:54:18,760 --> 00:54:22,878
- A bullet?
- That jumped up and bit you.

579
00:54:24,719 --> 00:54:28,235
Yes, sir.
Bit me directly in the but-tocks.

580
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:32,472
They said it was a million
dollar wound, but...

581
00:54:32,559 --> 00:54:34,516
The army must keep that money,

582
00:54:34,599 --> 00:54:38,228
'cause I still ain't seen a nickel
of that million dollars.

583
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:42,028
The only good thing
about being wounded in the but-tocks

584
00:54:42,119 --> 00:54:43,996
is the ice cream.

585
00:54:44,079 --> 00:54:48,231
They gave me all the ice cream
I could eat. And guess what?

586
00:54:48,320 --> 00:54:52,233
A good friend of mine was
in the bed right next door.

587
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:57,436
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

588
00:54:57,519 --> 00:55:00,478
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream!

589
00:55:11,079 --> 00:55:13,798
It's time for your bath,
Lieutenant.

590
00:55:22,039 --> 00:55:23,313
Harper!

591
00:55:26,519 --> 00:55:29,876
Cooper. Larson.

592
00:55:31,039 --> 00:55:34,827
Webster. Gump.

593
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:37,480
- Gump!
- I'm Forrest Gump.

594
00:55:40,079 --> 00:55:44,072
Kyle. Nichols.

595
00:55:45,519 --> 00:55:49,478
McMill. Johnson.

596
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:09,992
Gump, how can you watch
that stupid shit? Turn it off.

597
00:56:10,079 --> 00:56:12,753
You are tuned to the American Forces
Vietnam Network.

598
00:56:12,840 --> 00:56:15,114
This is Channel 6, Saigon.

599
00:56:17,760 --> 00:56:22,231
Good catch, Gump.
You know how to play this?

600
00:56:24,519 --> 00:56:27,034
Come on. Let me show you.

601
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:32,751
The secret to this game is
no matter what happens,

602
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:38,072
never, ever take your eye
off the ball.

603
00:56:39,679 --> 00:56:41,351
All right.

604
00:56:44,159 --> 00:56:47,994
For some reason, ping-pong
came very natural to me.

605
00:56:48,079 --> 00:56:51,277
See? Any idiot can play.

606
00:56:51,360 --> 00:56:53,635
So I started playing it all the time.

607
00:56:54,519 --> 00:56:59,547
I played ping-pong even when I didn't
have anyone to play ping-pong with.

608
00:57:07,840 --> 00:57:12,789
The hospital's people said it
made me look like a duck in water,

609
00:57:12,880 --> 00:57:14,518
whatever that means.

610
00:57:14,599 --> 00:57:17,797
Even Lieutenant Dan
would come and watch me play.

611
00:57:22,320 --> 00:57:27,552
I played ping-pong so much,
I even played it in my sleep.

612
00:57:34,280 --> 00:57:38,831
Now, you listen to me.
We all have a destiny.

613
00:57:38,920 --> 00:57:42,117
Nothing just happens.
It's all part of a plan!

614
00:57:42,199 --> 00:57:45,077
I should have died
out there with my men,

615
00:57:45,159 --> 00:57:50,108
but now, I'm nothing but
a goddamn cripple, a legless freak!

616
00:57:51,079 --> 00:57:54,117
Look. Look! Look at me!
You see that?

617
00:57:54,199 --> 00:57:57,954
Do you know what it's like
not to be able to use your legs?

618
00:58:00,639 --> 00:58:02,675
Yes, sir, I do.

619
00:58:05,960 --> 00:58:11,114
Did you hear what I said?
You cheated me! I had a destiny.

620
00:58:11,199 --> 00:58:14,875
I was supposed to die in the field
with honour!

621
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:19,911
That was my destiny,
and you cheated me out of it!

622
00:58:27,960 --> 00:58:30,315
You understand what I'm saying, Gump?

623
00:58:33,400 --> 00:58:40,237
This wasn't supposed to happen,
not to me. I had a destiny.

624
00:58:42,320 --> 00:58:46,710
I was Lieutenant Dan Taylor.

625
00:58:51,920 --> 00:58:55,594
You're still Lieutenant Dan.

626
00:59:16,840 --> 00:59:21,311
Look at me.
What am I going to do now?

627
00:59:24,519 --> 00:59:27,398
What am I going to do now?

628
00:59:36,599 --> 00:59:38,795
PFC Gump?

629
00:59:39,880 --> 00:59:42,996
- Yes, sir!
- As you were.

630
00:59:44,079 --> 00:59:47,675
Son, you been awarded
the Medal of Honour.

631
00:59:47,760 --> 00:59:52,880
Guess what, Lieutenant Dan?
They want to give me a med...

632
00:59:58,280 --> 01:00:02,637
Ma'am, what did they do
with Lieutenant Dan?

633
01:00:02,719 --> 01:00:04,516
They sent him home.

634
01:00:10,760 --> 01:00:13,911
Two weeks later, I left Vietnam.

635
01:00:14,000 --> 01:00:17,469
The ceremony was kicked off
with a candid speech by the President

636
01:00:17,559 --> 01:00:21,268
regarding the need for further
escalation of the war in Vietnam.

637
01:00:21,360 --> 01:00:24,715
President Johnson awarded four medals
of honour to men from each...

638
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:27,518
America owes you
a debt of gratitude, son.

639
01:00:29,400 --> 01:00:33,074
I understand you were wounded.
Where were you hit?

640
01:00:33,159 --> 01:00:34,751
In the but-tocks, sir.

641
01:00:34,840 --> 01:00:39,197
Well, that must be a sight.
I'd kinda like to see that.

642
01:00:51,559 --> 01:00:53,311
God damn, son!

643
01:00:56,159 --> 01:00:59,356
After that, Mama went
to the hotel to lay down,

644
01:00:59,440 --> 01:01:03,228
so I went out for a walk
to see our capital.

645
01:01:03,320 --> 01:01:08,030
Hilary! I got the vets.
What do you want to do with them?

646
01:01:08,119 --> 01:01:10,509
It's a good thing Mama was resting,

647
01:01:10,599 --> 01:01:13,398
'cause the streets was
awful crowded with people

648
01:01:13,480 --> 01:01:16,277
lookin' at all the statues
and monuments,

649
01:01:16,360 --> 01:01:18,429
and some of them people
were loud and pushy.

650
01:01:18,519 --> 01:01:20,954
OK, follow me! Move it out!

651
01:01:21,039 --> 01:01:24,271
Everywhere I went,
I had to stand in line.

652
01:01:30,760 --> 01:01:32,829
Come on. Go!

653
01:01:41,320 --> 01:01:45,916
You're a good man
for doing this. Good.

654
01:01:46,000 --> 01:01:48,036
OK.

655
01:01:48,119 --> 01:01:50,076
There was this man
giving a little talk.

656
01:01:50,159 --> 01:01:54,472
And for some reason, he was wearing
an American flag for a shirt.

657
01:01:56,079 --> 01:01:59,789
And he liked to say
the "F" Word a lot.

658
01:01:59,880 --> 01:02:02,110
"F" This and "F" That.

659
01:02:02,199 --> 01:02:07,512
And every time he said the "F" Word,
people, for some reason, cheered.

660
01:02:13,599 --> 01:02:16,512
Come on, man. Come up here, man.

661
01:02:16,599 --> 01:02:20,114
Come on. Come on. Yeah, you!
Come on. Move, move!

662
01:02:21,599 --> 01:02:23,476
Go on. Let's get up there.

663
01:02:35,480 --> 01:02:38,313
Tell us a little bit
about the war, man.

664
01:02:38,400 --> 01:02:44,713
- The war in Vietnam?
- The war in Viet-fuckin'-nam!

665
01:03:07,719 --> 01:03:09,072
Well...

666
01:03:09,159 --> 01:03:13,391
There was only one thing
I could say about the war in Vietnam.

667
01:03:13,480 --> 01:03:17,597
There's only one thing
I can say about the war in Vietnam.

668
01:03:21,119 --> 01:03:22,916
In Vietnam...

669
01:03:33,480 --> 01:03:35,356
What the hell are you do...

670
01:03:35,440 --> 01:03:38,193
I'll beat your head in,
you goddamn oinker!

671
01:03:38,280 --> 01:03:40,588
Jesus Christ!
What did they do with this?

672
01:03:41,519 --> 01:03:43,431
Can't hear you!

673
01:03:44,199 --> 01:03:46,235
Can't hear anything!

674
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:49,197
This... This one! Give me that!

675
01:03:49,280 --> 01:03:51,748
Speak up!

676
01:03:51,840 --> 01:03:53,637
That's it.

677
01:03:53,719 --> 01:03:58,235
And that's all I have to say
about that.

678
01:04:03,719 --> 01:04:07,315
That's so right on, man.
You said it all.

679
01:04:08,840 --> 01:04:13,833
- What's your name, man?
- My name is Forrest. Forrest Gump.

680
01:04:14,320 --> 01:04:17,231
- Forrest Gump.
- Gump!

681
01:04:54,599 --> 01:04:58,309
It was the happiest moment
of my life.

682
01:04:59,599 --> 01:05:03,228
Jenny and me were just
like peas and carrots again.

683
01:05:04,800 --> 01:05:08,952
She showed me around and introduced
me to some of her new friends.

684
01:05:09,039 --> 01:05:12,315
Shut that blind, man! And get your
white ass away from that window.

685
01:05:12,400 --> 01:05:14,675
Don't you know we in a war here?

686
01:05:14,760 --> 01:05:18,434
- He's cool. He's one of us.
- Let me tell you about us.

687
01:05:18,519 --> 01:05:20,635
Our purpose here
is to protect our black leaders

688
01:05:20,719 --> 01:05:22,630
from the racial onslaught of the pig

689
01:05:22,719 --> 01:05:24,597
who wishes to brutalise
our black leaders,

690
01:05:24,679 --> 01:05:28,559
rape our women,
and destroy our black communities.

691
01:05:29,719 --> 01:05:33,793
- Who's the baby killer?
- This is my friend I told you about.

692
01:05:33,880 --> 01:05:36,677
This is Forrest Gump.
Forrest, this is Wesley.

693
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:39,148
Wesley and I
lived together in Berkeley,

694
01:05:39,239 --> 01:05:42,038
and he's the president
of the Berkeley chapter of SDS.

695
01:05:42,119 --> 01:05:44,918
We are here to offer
protection and help

696
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:48,231
for all those who need our help,
because we, the Black Panthers,

697
01:05:48,320 --> 01:05:50,675
are against the war in Vietnam.

698
01:05:50,760 --> 01:05:53,717
We are against any war where black
soldiers are sent to the front line

699
01:05:53,800 --> 01:05:55,597
to die for a country that hates them.

700
01:05:55,679 --> 01:05:59,355
We are against any war
where black soldiers go to fight

701
01:05:59,440 --> 01:06:03,068
and come to be brutalised
and killed in their own communities.

702
01:06:03,159 --> 01:06:06,675
We are against all these racist
and imperial acts...

703
01:06:21,360 --> 01:06:24,909
Forrest! Stop it! Stop it!

704
01:06:33,320 --> 01:06:35,788
I shouldn't have brought you here.

705
01:06:35,880 --> 01:06:39,713
I should have known it was going
to be some bullshit hassle!

