Take a left! Left!

937
01:29:54,800 --> 01:29:58,712
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

938
01:29:59,600 --> 01:30:01,511
That's where we'll find them.

939
01:30:13,600 --> 01:30:17,354
- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
- OK, so I was wrong.

940
01:30:17,439 --> 01:30:20,238
How are we going to find them?

941
01:30:20,319 --> 01:30:23,948
Maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

942
01:30:30,079 --> 01:30:32,514
So I went to church every Sunday.

943
01:30:33,960 --> 01:30:39,478
Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came too,
though he left the praying up to me.

944
01:30:53,560 --> 01:30:58,680
- No shrimp.
- Where the hell's this God of yours?

945
01:30:58,760 --> 01:31:03,595
It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
'cause right then God showed up.

946
01:31:19,840 --> 01:31:22,229
You'll never sink this boat!

947
01:31:22,319 --> 01:31:28,189
Now, me, I was scared,
but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.

948
01:31:28,279 --> 01:31:30,588
Come on!

949
01:31:32,479 --> 01:31:38,112
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

950
01:31:39,880 --> 01:31:47,069
It's time for a showdown! You and me!
I'm right here! Come and get me!

951
01:31:49,239 --> 01:31:52,868
You'll never sink this boat!

952
01:31:55,039 --> 01:31:56,996
Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,

953
01:31:57,079 --> 01:31:59,149
destroying nearly everything
in its path.

954
01:31:59,239 --> 01:32:02,037
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

955
01:32:02,119 --> 01:32:04,554
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

956
01:32:04,640 --> 01:32:09,634
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

957
01:32:09,720 --> 01:32:11,233
This reporter has learned,

958
01:32:11,319 --> 01:32:14,994
in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.

959
01:32:15,079 --> 01:32:17,435
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

960
01:32:17,520 --> 01:32:20,478
After that, shrimping was easy.

961
01:32:26,039 --> 01:32:28,917
Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails

962
01:32:29,000 --> 01:32:33,152
and barbecues and all, and we were
the only boat left standing,

963
01:32:33,239 --> 01:32:38,394
Bubba-Gump shrimp's what they got.
We got a whole bunch of boats.

964
01:32:38,479 --> 01:32:40,470
Twelve Jennys, big old warehouse.

965
01:32:40,560 --> 01:32:44,677
We even have hats
that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

966
01:32:44,760 --> 01:32:47,274
Bubba-Gump Shrimp. A household name.

967
01:32:47,359 --> 01:32:49,032
Hold on there, boy.

968
01:32:49,119 --> 01:32:53,636
Are you telling me you're the owner
of the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

969
01:32:53,720 --> 01:32:56,518
Yes. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

970
01:32:56,600 --> 01:33:01,627
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time, but that tops them all.

971
01:33:04,119 --> 01:33:07,475
We were sitting
next to a millionaire.

972
01:33:10,319 --> 01:33:15,234
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

973
01:33:15,319 --> 01:33:20,234
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

974
01:33:20,319 --> 01:33:24,154
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

975
01:33:24,239 --> 01:33:26,470
Yes, I would.

976
01:33:30,600 --> 01:33:32,351
That's him right there.

977
01:33:34,359 --> 01:33:37,158
Let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan.

978
01:33:43,600 --> 01:33:47,672
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

979
01:34:12,319 --> 01:34:18,350
He never actually said so, but
I think he made his peace with God.

980
01:34:25,880 --> 01:34:27,631
For the second time in 17 days,

981
01:34:27,720 --> 01:34:31,155
President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.

982
01:34:31,239 --> 01:34:35,676
- Base to Jenny 1. Base to Jenny 1.
- Jenny 1. Go, Margo.

983
01:34:35,760 --> 01:34:37,591
Forrest has a phone call.

984
01:34:37,680 --> 01:34:40,069
Well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

985
01:34:40,159 --> 01:34:44,516
- He is indisposed at the moment.
- His mama's sick.

986
01:35:02,479 --> 01:35:05,516
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

987
01:35:07,479 --> 01:35:09,550
Hi, Forrest.

988
01:35:09,640 --> 01:35:13,076
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

989
01:35:19,279 --> 01:35:22,795
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

990
01:35:33,640 --> 01:35:37,757
- What's the matter, Mama?
- I'm dying, Forrest.

991
01:35:40,079 --> 01:35:42,877
Come on in, sit down over here.

992
01:35:55,920 --> 01:36:02,268
- Why are you dying, Mama?
- It's my time. It's just my time.

993
01:36:04,079 --> 01:36:08,118
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

994
01:36:09,800 --> 01:36:14,748
Death is just a part of life.
Something we're all destined to do.

995
01:36:15,920 --> 01:36:20,993
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

996
01:36:21,079 --> 01:36:25,551
- I did the best I could.
- You did good.

997
01:36:25,640 --> 01:36:31,317
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

998
01:36:31,760 --> 01:36:36,150
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

999
01:36:39,479 --> 01:36:41,993
What's my destiny, Mama?

1000
01:36:42,079 --> 01:36:46,358
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1001
01:36:47,640 --> 01:36:50,472
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1002
01:36:50,560 --> 01:36:53,313
You never know
what you're going to get.

1003
01:36:53,399 --> 01:36:57,472
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

1004
01:36:57,560 --> 01:36:59,515
I will miss you, Forrest.

1005
01:37:01,119 --> 01:37:05,238
She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.

1006
01:37:05,319 --> 01:37:09,836
I bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.

1007
01:37:12,800 --> 01:37:15,792
And that's all
I have to say about that.

1008
01:37:22,199 --> 01:37:24,953
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1009
01:37:25,039 --> 01:37:28,112
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1010
01:37:30,880 --> 01:37:35,158
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1011
01:37:35,239 --> 01:37:38,073
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1012
01:37:38,159 --> 01:37:41,868
and a college graduate, the city
fathers of Greenbow, Alabama,

1013
01:37:41,960 --> 01:37:44,554
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1014
01:37:46,119 --> 01:37:49,192
So I never went back
to work for Lieutenant Dan,

1015
01:37:49,279 --> 01:37:51,953
though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1016
01:37:52,039 --> 01:37:56,271
He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1017
01:37:56,359 --> 01:37:59,875
I got a call from him saying we don't
have to worry about money no more,

1018
01:37:59,960 --> 01:38:04,158
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1019
01:38:06,039 --> 01:38:09,998
Now Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1020
01:38:10,079 --> 01:38:13,310
and the rest is just for showing off.

1021
01:38:13,399 --> 01:38:18,712
So I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare Gospel Church.

1022
01:38:19,439 --> 01:38:24,274
And I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1023
01:38:25,720 --> 01:38:31,317
And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,

1024
01:38:31,399 --> 01:38:35,074
I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.

1025
01:38:37,319 --> 01:38:38,912
You know what?

1026
01:38:39,000 --> 01:38:42,833
She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.

1027
01:38:42,920 --> 01:38:45,309
That smells wonderful.

1028
01:38:45,399 --> 01:38:50,520
And 'cause I was a gozillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1029
01:38:50,600 --> 01:38:52,670
I cut that grass for free.

1030
01:38:55,239 --> 01:38:58,630
But at night-time
when there was nothing to do

1031
01:38:58,720 --> 01:39:03,555
and the house was all empty,
I'd always think of Jenny.

1032
01:40:04,880 --> 01:40:08,189
And then, she was there.

1033
01:40:39,880 --> 01:40:43,475
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1034
01:40:53,800 --> 01:40:56,757
Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1035
01:40:56,840 --> 01:41:01,470
Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1036
01:41:01,560 --> 01:41:05,347
or maybe it was because she was
so tired, 'cause she went to bed

1037
01:41:05,439 --> 01:41:09,877
and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.

1038
01:41:10,560 --> 01:41:12,676
It was wonderful having her home.

1039
01:41:12,760 --> 01:41:19,029
Every day we'd take a walk, and I'd
jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1040
01:41:19,119 --> 01:41:21,872
and she'd listen about
ping-ponging and shrimping

1041
01:41:21,960 --> 01:41:25,747
and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
I did all the talking.

1042
01:41:25,840 --> 01:41:29,115
Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.

1043
01:42:07,079 --> 01:42:09,832
How could you do this?

1044
01:42:45,439 --> 01:42:49,796
Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.

1045
01:42:49,880 --> 01:42:55,511
I never really knew
why she came back, but I didn't care.

1046
01:42:55,600 --> 01:43:00,150
It was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.

1047
01:43:01,520 --> 01:43:05,479
Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,

1048
01:43:07,640 --> 01:43:11,997
and she gave me the best gift anyone
could ever get in the wide world.

1049
01:43:12,079 --> 01:43:14,036
They're just for running.

1050
01:43:17,600 --> 01:43:20,636
And she even showed me how to dance.

1051
01:43:30,119 --> 01:43:34,033
Well, we was like family,
Jenny and me...

1052
01:43:36,800 --> 01:43:39,997
and it was the happiest time
in my life.

1053
01:44:03,279 --> 01:44:07,158
You done watching it?
I'm going to bed.

1054
01:44:17,600 --> 01:44:19,829
Will you marry me?

1055
01:44:23,840 --> 01:44:27,115
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1056
01:44:29,600 --> 01:44:31,476
You would, Forrest.

1057
01:44:33,359 --> 01:44:35,510
But you won't marry me.

1058
01:44:37,359 --> 01:44:40,078
You don't want to marry me.

1059
01:44:43,039 --> 01:44:45,349
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1060
01:44:50,359 --> 01:44:56,037
I'm not a smart man,
but I know what love is.

1061
01:45:35,119 --> 01:45:37,953
Forrest, I do love you.

1062
01:46:27,920 --> 01:46:33,153
- Where are you running off to?
- I'm not running.

1063
01:48:00,039 --> 01:48:05,398
That day, for no particular reason,
I decided to go for a little run.

1064
01:48:05,800 --> 01:48:09,429
So I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there

1065
01:48:09,520 --> 01:48:12,079
I thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.

1066
01:48:12,159 --> 01:48:14,878
President Carter,
suffering from heat exhaustion...

1067
01:48:14,960 --> 01:48:16,677
And when I got there,

1068
01:48:16,760 --> 01:48:20,752
I thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.

1069
01:48:20,840 --> 01:48:23,229
Now, thinking since I'd run this far,

1070
01:48:23,319 --> 01:48:26,994
maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.

1071
01:48:27,079 --> 01:48:30,595
And that's what I did.
I ran clear across Alabama.

1072
01:48:30,680 --> 01:48:34,194
No particular reason.
I just kept on going.

1073
01:48:34,920 --> 01:48:36,911
I ran clear to the ocean.

1074
01:48:42,239 --> 01:48:46,198
And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1075
01:48:46,279 --> 01:48:49,351
might as well turn around,
just keep on going.

1076
01:48:52,720 --> 01:48:56,952
And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1077
01:48:58,960 --> 01:49:02,395
I might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.

1078
01:49:02,479 --> 01:49:07,759
When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.

1079
01:49:07,840 --> 01:49:13,233
When I had to go...
you know... I went.

1080
01:49:13,760 --> 01:49:18,993
- And so, you just ran.
- Yeah.

1081
01:49:53,319 --> 01:49:58,952
I'd think a lot about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.

1082
01:49:59,039 --> 01:50:04,989
But most of all, I thought about
Jenny. I thought about her a lot.

1083
01:50:06,600 --> 01:50:10,149
For more than two years,
a man named Forrest Gump,

1084
01:50:10,239 --> 01:50:12,800
a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,

1085
01:50:12,880 --> 01:50:17,112
has been running across America.
Charles Cooper reports.

1086
01:50:17,199 --> 01:50:20,317
For the fourth time
on his journey across America,

1087
01:50:20,399 --> 01:50:24,996
Forrest Gump the gardener will cross
the Mississippi River again today.

1088
01:50:26,359 --> 01:50:29,750
- I'll be damned. Forrest?
- Why are you running?

1089
01:50:29,840 --> 01:50:33,229
- Are you doing this for world peace?
- For the homeless?

1090
01:50:33,319 --> 01:50:36,118
- Are you running for women's rights?
- The environment?

1091
01:50:36,199 --> 01:50:40,909
They couldn't believe somebody would
do all that running for no reason.

1092
01:50:41,000 --> 01:50:45,118
- Why are you doing this?
- I just felt like running.

1093
01:50:45,199 --> 01:50:46,712
I just felt like runnin'.

1094
01:50:47,920 --> 01:50:51,229
It's you.
I can't believe it's really you.

1095
01:50:51,319 --> 01:50:56,599
For some reason, what I was doing
seemed to make sense to people.

1096
01:50:56,680 --> 01:50:58,988
It was like an alarm
went off in my head.

1097
01:50:59,079 --> 01:51:02,550
I said, "Here's a guy
that's got his act together.

1098
01:51:02,640 --> 01:51:06,394
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr Gump.

1099
01:51:06,479 --> 01:51:08,675
So I got company.

1100
01:51:10,159 --> 01:51:15,951
And after that, I got more company.
And then, even more people joined in.

1101
01:51:18,039 --> 01:51:21,032
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1102
01:51:24,359 --> 01:51:26,315
I don't know anything about that,

1103
01:51:26,399 --> 01:51:30,756
but some of those people asked me
if I could help them out.

1104
01:51:30,840 --> 01:51:35,152
I was wondering if you might help me.
I'm in the bumper sticker business.

1105
01:51:35,239 --> 01:51:38,595
I need a good slogan, and since
you've been so inspirational,

1106
01:51:38,680 --> 01:51:41,113
I thought
you might be able to help me...

1107
01:51:41,199 --> 01:51:45,193
Whoa, man! You just ran
through a big pile of dog shit!

1108
01:51:46,399 --> 01:51:50,279
- It happens.
- What, shit?

1109
01:51:50,359 --> 01:51:52,112
Sometimes.

1110
01:51:53,880 --> 01:51:57,235
And some years later, I heard
that that fella did come up

1111
01:51:57,319 --> 01:52:01,551
with a bumper sticker slogan
and made a lot of money off of it.

1112
01:52:01,640 --> 01:52:03,835
Another time, I was running along,

1113
01:52:03,920 --> 01:52:06,559
somebody who'd lost all his money
in the t-shirt business,

1114
01:52:06,640 --> 01:52:09,837
he wanted to put my face
on a t-shirt,

1115
01:52:09,920 --> 01:52:13,673
but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.

1116
01:52:13,760 --> 01:52:17,149
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that colour anyway.

1117
01:52:21,119 --> 01:52:22,872
Have a nice day.

1118
01:52:24,600 --> 01:52:27,876
Some years later,
I found out that that man did come up

1119
01:52:27,960 --> 01:52:31,747
with an idea for a t-shirt.
He made a lot of money.

1120
01:52:34,159 --> 01:52:38,869
Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.

1121
01:52:38,960 --> 01:52:45,229
Mama always said, "Put the past
behind you before you can move on."

1122
01:52:45,680 --> 01:52:49,434
And I think
that's what my running was all about.

1123
01:52:50,840 --> 01:52:56,869
I had run for three years,
two months, 14 days and 16 hours.

1124
01:53:11,960 --> 01:53:14,109
Quiet. Quiet.
He's going to say something.

1125
01:53:25,359 --> 01:53:27,635
I'm pretty tired.

1126
01:53:29,880 --> 01:53:32,189
Think I'll go home now.

1127
01:53:48,960 --> 01:53:51,394
Now what are we supposed to do?

1128
01:53:52,600 --> 01:53:57,354
And just like that,
my runnin' days was over.

1129
01:53:57,439 --> 01:53:59,590
So I went home to Alabama.

1130
01:54:01,279 --> 01:54:05,431
Moments ago, at 2.25 p.m., as
President Reagan was leaving the...

1131
01:54:07,359 --> 01:54:11,194
...five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.

1132
01:54:11,279 --> 01:54:13,475
The President was shot
in the chest...

1133
01:54:13,560 --> 01:54:15,311
I picked up the mail.

1134
01:54:15,399 --> 01:54:19,837
And one day, out of the blue clear
sky, I got a letter from Jenny

1135
01:54:19,920 --> 01:54:23,595
wondering if I could come down
to Savannah and see her,

1136
01:54:23,680 --> 01:54:25,671
and that's what I'm doing here.

1137
01:54:26,960 --> 01:54:28,951
She saw me on TV, running.

1138
01:54:29,039 --> 01:54:33,271
I'm supposed to go on the number nine
bus to Richmond Street

1139
01:54:33,359 --> 01:54:39,958
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, apartment 4.

1140
01:54:40,039 --> 01:54:43,395
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1141
01:54:43,479 --> 01:54:48,314
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1142
01:54:49,239 --> 01:54:52,073
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1143
01:54:53,840 --> 01:54:56,194
It was nice talking to you.

1144
01:54:58,399 --> 01:55:00,708
I hope everything works out for you!

1145
01:55:11,680 --> 01:55:16,195
- How you doin'? Come in! Come in!
- I got your letter.

1146
01:55:16,279 --> 01:55:22,037
- I was wondering about that.
- This your house?

1147
01:55:22,119 --> 01:55:25,078
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1148
01:55:25,159 --> 01:55:28,835
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1149
01:55:34,720 --> 01:55:37,951
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1150
01:55:39,920 --> 01:55:45,789
I kept a scrapbook of your clippings,
and everything. There you are.

1151
01:55:47,560 --> 01:55:49,470
And this, I got you running.

1152
01:55:51,760 --> 01:55:56,310
I ran a long way. It's a long time.

1153
01:55:58,680 --> 01:56:00,716
And there...

1154
01:56:06,359 --> 01:56:09,829
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this.

1155
01:56:12,079 --> 01:56:17,518
I just I want to apologise
for anything that I ever did to you

1156
01:56:17,600 --> 01:56:21,434
'cause I was messed up
for a long time, and...

1157
01:56:24,880 --> 01:56:27,599
- Hi.
- Hey, you.

1158
01:56:27,680 --> 01:56:30,637
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1159
01:56:30,800 --> 01:56:34,109
Next week my schedule changes,
so I can...

1160
01:56:34,199 --> 01:56:36,395
No problem. Got to go.
I'm double-parked.

1161
01:56:36,479 --> 01:56:38,277
OK. Thanks.

1162
01:56:39,960 --> 01:56:43,668
This is my very good friend Mr Gump.
Can you say hi?

1163
01:56:43,760 --> 01:56:46,114
- Hello, Mr Gump.
- Hello.

1164
01:56:46,199 --> 01:56:50,078
- Can I go watch TV now?
- Yes. Just keep it low.

1165
01:56:52,199 --> 01:56:55,271
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1166
01:56:58,479 --> 01:57:02,154
- His name's Forrest.
- Like me!

1167
01:57:04,359 --> 01:57:09,036
- I named him after his daddy.
- He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1168
01:57:10,600 --> 01:57:12,954
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1169
01:57:28,960 --> 01:57:32,315
Forrest, look at me.
Look at me, Forrest.

1170
01:57:33,600 --> 01:57:39,277
There's nothing you need to do.
You didn't do anything wrong. OK?

1171
01:57:43,680 --> 01:57:45,431
Isn't he beautiful?

1172
01:57:46,680 --> 01:57:50,672
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1173
01:57:53,439 --> 01:57:55,192
But...

1174
01:57:58,199 --> 01:58:00,315
Is he smart? Can he...

1175
01:58:00,399 --> 01:58:04,791
He's very smart. He's one
of the smartest in his class.

1176
01:58:12,920 --> 01:58:15,592
Yeah, it's OK. Go talk to him.

1177
01:58:24,439 --> 01:58:27,876
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1178
01:58:49,399 --> 01:58:53,677
Forrest, I'm sick.

1179
01:58:56,119 --> 01:58:59,475
What, do you have
a cough due to a cold?

1180
01:58:59,560 --> 01:59:04,634
I have some virus, and the doctors,
they don't know what it is,

1181
01:59:04,720 --> 01:59:07,756
and there isn't
anything they can do about it.

1182
01:59:12,399 --> 01:59:14,833
You could come home with me.

1183
01:59:17,199 --> 01:59:22,149
You and little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1184
01:59:25,439 --> 01:59:28,398
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1185
01:59:29,840 --> 01:59:32,512
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1186
01:59:37,600 --> 01:59:38,953
OK.

1187
01:59:40,600 --> 01:59:42,078
Please take your seats.

1188
01:59:45,399 --> 01:59:48,311
Forrest? It's time to start.

1189
02:00:06,319 --> 02:00:09,551
Hi. Your tie.

1190
02:00:21,960 --> 02:00:24,154
Lieutenant Dan.

1191
02:00:38,319 --> 02:00:42,198
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hello, Forrest.

1192
02:00:42,560 --> 02:00:46,234
You got new legs. New legs!

1193
02:00:47,479 --> 02:00:51,109
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1194
02:00:51,199 --> 02:00:55,351
Titanium alloy. It's what they use
on the space shuttle.

1195
02:00:58,600 --> 02:01:00,555
Magic legs.

1196
02:01:02,319 --> 02:01:06,631
This is my fiancÃ©e, Susan.

1197
02:01:09,000 --> 02:01:13,551
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1198
02:01:13,640 --> 02:01:20,556
- Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.
- Hi. It's nice to meet you finally.

1199
02:01:30,680 --> 02:01:34,592
Do you, Forrest, take Jenny
to be your wife?

1200
02:01:36,239 --> 02:01:40,233
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1201
02:01:41,800 --> 02:01:45,076
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1202
02:02:14,600 --> 02:02:17,432
- Hey.
- Hi.

1203
02:02:35,720 --> 02:02:38,234
Were you scared in Vietnam?

1204
02:02:39,520 --> 02:02:43,877
Yes. Well, I don't know.

1205
02:02:44,960 --> 02:02:50,238
Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out.

1206
02:02:52,960 --> 02:02:54,837
And then it was nice.

1207
02:02:58,079 --> 02:03:02,391
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1208
02:03:02,479 --> 02:03:07,189
There was always
a million sparkles on the water.

1209
02:03:08,760 --> 02:03:12,354
Like that mountain lake.
It was so clear, Jenny,

1210
02:03:12,439 --> 02:03:17,594
it looked like there were two skies
one on top of the other.

1211
02:03:19,159 --> 02:03:22,470
And then in the desert,
when the sun comes up,

1212
02:03:25,319 --> 02:03:31,509
I couldn't tell where heaven stopped
and the earth began.

1213
02:03:32,880 --> 02:03:35,074
It was so beautiful.

1214
02:03:39,119 --> 02:03:41,917
I wish I could've been there
with you.

1215
02:03:45,039 --> 02:03:46,951
You were.

1216
02:03:56,680 --> 02:03:58,431
I love you.

1217
02:04:02,279 --> 02:04:05,317
You died on a Saturday morning.

1218
02:04:07,079 --> 02:04:11,073
And I had you placed
here under our tree.

1219
02:04:15,319 --> 02:04:20,837
And I had that house of your father's
bulldozed to the ground.

1220
02:04:24,479 --> 02:04:31,396
Mama always said
that dyin' was a part of life.

1221
02:04:34,520 --> 02:04:36,670
I sure wish it wasn't.

1222
02:04:39,479 --> 02:04:43,519
Little Forrest is doing just fine.

1223
02:04:46,399 --> 02:04:48,868
About to start school again soon,

1224
02:04:49,840 --> 02:04:53,992
and I make his breakfast,
lunch, and dinner every day.

1225
02:04:55,760 --> 02:05:01,710
I make sure he combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1226
02:05:04,239 --> 02:05:10,109
Teaching him how to play ping-pong.
He's really good.

1227
02:05:10,199 --> 02:05:12,155
Forrest, you go.

1228
02:05:16,720 --> 02:05:18,836
We fish a lot.

1229
02:05:22,039 --> 02:05:25,715
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1230
02:05:28,000 --> 02:05:32,835
You'd be so proud of him. I am.

1231
02:05:34,159 --> 02:05:37,118
He wrote you a letter.

1232
02:05:38,600 --> 02:05:40,636
And he says I can't read it.

1233
02:05:40,720 --> 02:05:44,599
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1234
02:06:06,399 --> 02:06:12,235
I don't know if mama was right
or if it's Lieutenant Dan.

1235
02:06:13,119 --> 02:06:19,719
I don't know if
we each have a destiny,

1236
02:06:19,800 --> 02:06:26,319
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeze.

1237
02:06:30,560 --> 02:06:35,350
But I think maybe it's both.

1238
02:06:39,960 --> 02:06:43,110
Maybe both is happening
at the same time.

1239
02:06:48,560 --> 02:06:50,436
But I miss you, Jenny.

1240
02:06:56,600 --> 02:07:01,115
If there's anything you need,
I won't be far away.

1241
02:07:34,600 --> 02:07:38,274
Here's your bus. OK.

1242
02:07:40,279 --> 02:07:42,190
I know this.

1243
02:07:42,279 --> 02:07:44,953
I'm gonna share that for
show-and-tell

1244
02:07:45,039 --> 02:07:47,679
because Grandma
used to read it to you.

1245
02:07:47,760 --> 02:07:49,716
My favourite book.

1246
02:07:56,600 --> 02:07:58,795
Here you go.

1247
02:08:05,520 --> 02:08:06,918
Don't...

1248
02:08:09,000 --> 02:08:13,993
- I want to tell you I love you.
- I love you, too, Daddy.

1249
02:08:14,079 --> 02:08:17,152
I'll be right here when you get back.

1250
02:08:21,479 --> 02:08:25,712
You understand this is
the bus to school, don't you?

1251
02:08:25,800 --> 02:08:30,430
Of course, and you're Dorothy Harris,
and I'm Forrest Gump.
